7 Problem Statement:Develop an Android application for a College Event Registration system using Intents, Events, Listeners, and Adapters. The first activity should display a list of events using a ListView or RecyclerView with an Adapter. On selecting an event, the application must handle the click using a Listener and navigate to the second activity through an Intent while passing the event name. The second activity should display the selected event and contain a Register button which, on click, shows a confirmation message using Toast or AlertDialog.
Aim:To develop an Android application that demonstrates the implementation of Intents, Events, Listeners, and Adapters by creating a College Event Registration system that enables navigation between activities, handles user interactions, and displays data using Adapter-based views.
